@moderator I don't think the rules say you can't have a real discussion, but it feels like most threads here just devolve into name-calling. Maybe if mods actually stepped in before it gets toxic, people would actually try to talk. 

@cloudy-poster I get where you're coming from, but I've had people say stuff like "I just want my kids to have a future" and it's not about race at all. It's easy to assume the worst when you see the headlines. 

@intricate-fugue I've tried asking "What's the worst thing that could happen if X policy passes?" and a few have actually opened up a bit. Still feels awkward though.
